default1.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultRobert Bosch Healthcare offers a wide ranging portfolio of care products for chronically ill patients and the elderly which helps to bring significant quality, efficiency and financial gains to the UK healthcare sector.
default 
defaultOur aim is to help people with long term conditions remain in their own homes and out of hospital wherever possible.
default 
default1.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBosch’s telehealth spectrum ranges from 
defaultin-home 
defaultpatient terminals to comprehensive software allowing healthcare professionals to efficiently evaluate 
defaultrisk-stratified 
defaultdata coming from the patient terminals and other connected devices. Bosch Telehealth strives to improve 
defaultthe care and management of patients with long-term conditions 
defaultthrough systematic patient 
defaulteducation, behaviour modification support, daily 
defaultmonitoring 
defaultof symptoms and vital signs 
defaultand 
defaultpatient engagement techniques
default. The result is that health professionals are able to provide a higher quality of care for patients with chronic conditions, patients lead happier and healthier lives, and the cost of healthcare is reduced for funders. Robert Bosch Healthcare
default Systems
default, Inc. is a fully-owned subsidiary of the Bosch Group.
default1.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Bosch Group is a leading global supplier of technology and services
default and is represented in over 60 countries
default.
default The company was set up in Stuttgart in 1886 by Robert Bosch (1861
default–
default1942) as a “Workshop for Precision Mechanics and Electrical Engineering.” The special ownership structure of Robert Bosch GmbH guarantees the entrepreneurial freedom of the Bosch Group, making it possible for the company to plan over the long term and to undertake significant up-front investments in the safeguarding of its future. Ninety-two 
defaultper cent
default of the share capital of Robert Bosch GmbH is held by Robert Bosch 
defaultStiftung
default GmbH, a charitable foundation.
