default2.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe respected health 
defaultthink-tank
default, 2020health, recently published the findings of its own study of a telehealth hub pilot in Yorkshire.
default 
defaultIt found that 
defaulttelehealth
default-enabled care co-ordination can reduce hospital admissions, provide care at home and improve patient outcomes.
default 
defaultIt noted that for every 100 patients using technology, 10 hospital admissions are averted each month – that's up to £2,000 saved per averted admission, representing a return on investment of 48%.
default2.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Department of Health (DH) believes that at least three million people with long term conditions and/or social care needs could benefit from the use of assistive technologies and telehealth services.
default2.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultImplemented effectively these technologies can alleviate pressure on long term NHS 
defaultand social care 
defaultcosts and improve people’s quality of life through better self-care in the home setting.
