default4.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBosch was disappointed with the 
defaultsecond stage results of the
default WSD and its apparent limited effect on quality of life and psychological outcomes. Bosch 
defaulttelehealth 
defaultsystems have demonstrated, in more than 40 publications, that its content-driven telehealth intervention supports integrated care and 
defaultconsistently 
defaultproduces significant cost savings in addition to improve
defaultment
default in both clinical outcomes and the quality of care.
default 
default4.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBosch Healthcare’s Health Buddy System (HBS) was not part of the WSD project and provides 
defaulta
default more
default integrated solution 
defaultthan the telehealth interventions used in the WSD.
default 
defaultWhilst many systems focus on vital signs monitoring, Bosch systems utilise 
defaultmore extensive education to support improved patient self-management, positive reinforcement of beha
defaultviour change which is personalis
defaulted to the patient
default.
default 
default4.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhilst a significant study for telehealth in the UK, there are several mitigating factors that need to be considered
default when reviewing the results of the WSD
default.
default 
defaultFor example, 
defaulttelehealth
default devices and monitoring systems varied amongst the study sites and there were inconsistencies in describing exactly what the 
defaulttelehealth
default interventions were.
default 
defaultCrucially
default none of the systems used provided
default support for increased efficiency and effectiveness of clinician workflow
default or supported improved patient self-management
default.
