default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWith a
defaultn
default ageing population on the one hand and ongoing budget restrictions on the other, the results have called into perspective an ever-more-urgent need to look at how to create a sustainable delivery model for the future.
default5.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTherefore UK health and social care services must also look abroad for the evidence base to support a more integrated approach 
defaultto 
defaultmanaging long term conditions
default. 
defaultTo take the 
defaultexample 
defaultof a study from the USA 
defaultMedicare system (which has parallels with the NHS) that
default focussed on Congestive Heart Failure 
default(one of 
defaultthis Inquiry’s 
defaultterms of reference) 
defaultBosch found significant reduced mortality for patients through 
defaultthe use of its telehealth in combination with care coordination
default:
default 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default5.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDeveloping strategies to reduce readmission rates and improve outcomes for patients with HF has become a national health priorit
defaulty in the United States
default, as it has in other developed countries
default.
default5.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultData for 623 matched pairs of Medicare HF beneficiaries were 
defaultanalysed
default. The results showed that care management combined with the Health Buddy System was associated with a 25 
defaultper cent
default reduction in all-cause mortality risk in beneficiaries with HF, who were offered the 
defaultprogramme
default and a 57 
defaultper cent
default reduction in mortality risk for those HF beneficiaries who actively participated in the 
defaultprogramme
default compared to the control studies
default.
default5.5.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEmpowering patients does not only statistically influence health outcomes but has associated cost and social benefits too. Self-management helps reduce the cost burden on services through reducing the number of staff required per patient and in social terms the education component, common to many assistive technologies, greatly increases health literacy. The long term benefits of increased health literacy are exponential.
default5.6.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThese "on the ground" results are, more often than not, the product of integrated delivery systems being put into practice through healthcare and industry partnerships that handle populations with high numbers of people with chronic conditions.
default5.7.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFor technology to work, it must be embedded in care pathways that are designed for patients with long term conditions. It should comprise of a range of interventions 
default–
default including coaching and telecare. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default6.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBosch’s studies have demonstrated that, through giving patients an active role in their treatment, they can significantly influence their own health outcomes. Bosch believes that this will be vital to the future strategy of managing long term conditions. 
